  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Start by making the confit garlic. Heat the oven to 160°C. Peel the garlic cloves and put them in a small ovenproof dish, then cover them with olive oil so they’re totally submerged. Cover with a lid or kitchen foil and slide into the oven for 30-40 mins, or until the garlic cloves are golden brown and super soft. Remove from the oven and allow to cool. You can do this bit ahead of time!"
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "To make the dressing, combine the chipotle paste, mayonnaise, mustard and grated cheese in a bowl. Mix well and finely grate in the garlic clove. Add the zest and juice of the lemon and mix again. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Set aside."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Cut the focaccia into croutons and toss with olive oil. Tip into a frying pan and cook over a medium heat for 7-8 mins until golden brown and crispy. Set aside."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Roughly chop the kale, hispi, cucumber and lettuce. Add to a large bowl with the beans, chicken and parm. Tip in the croutons and dressing. Toss everything together and divide between plates. Add a few cloves of confit garlic to each plate and a drizzle of the garlicky oil. Finish with a couple of anchovies and a squeeze of lemon."
    }
  ],
